3035 /*
3036  * ehash_connect_bucket () - Connect bucket to directory
3037  * return: int NO_ERROR, or ER_FAILED
3038  * ehid(in): identifier for the extendible hashing structure
3039  * local_depth(in): local depth of the bucket; determines how many directory
3040  * pointers are set to point to the given bucket identifier
3041  * hash_key(in): pseudo key that led to the bucket page; determines which
3042  * pointers to be updated
3043  * bucket_vpid(in): Identifier of the bucket page to connect
3044  * is_temp(in): true if temporary (logging is not required)
3045  *
3046  * Note: This function connects the given bucket to the directory of
3047  * specified extendible hashing structure. All the directory
3048  * pointers whose number have the same value as the hash_key
3049  * for the first "local_depth" bits are updated with "bucket_vpid".
3050  * Since these pointers are successive to each other, it is
3051  * known that a contagious area (possibly over several pages)
3052  * on the directory will be updated. Thus, this function is
3053  * implemented in the following way: First, the directory pages
3054  * to be updated are determined. Then, these pages are retrieved,
3055  * updated and released one at a time. For recovery purposes, the
3056  * contents of these pages are logged before and after they are updated.
3057  */
3058 static int
3059 ehash_connect_bucket (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p, int local_depth, EHASH_HASH_KEY hash_key,
3060  VPID * bucket_vpid_p, bool is_temp)
3061 {
3062  EHASH_DIR_HEADER dir_header;
3063  EHASH_DIR_RECORD *dir_record_p;
3064  EHASH_REPETITION repetition;
3065  PAGE_PTR page_p;
3066  int location;
3067  int first_page, last_page;
3068  int first_ptr_offset, last_ptr_offset;
3069  int start_offset, end_offset;
3070  int diff;
3071  int i, j;
3072  int bef_length;
3073  unsigned int set_bits;
3074  unsigned int clear_bits;
3075 
3076  repetition.vpid = *bucket_vpid_p;
3077 
3078  page_p = ehash_fix_ehid_page (thread_p, ehid_p, PGBUF_LATCH_READ);
3079  if (page_p == NULL)
3080  {
3081  return ER_FAILED;
3082  }
3083 
3084  memcpy (&dir_header, page_p, EHASH_DIR_HEADER_SIZE);
3085  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_p);
3086 
3087  /* First find out how many page entries will be updated in the directory */
3088  location = GETBITS (hash_key, 1, dir_header.depth);
3089 
3090  diff = dir_header.depth - local_depth;
3091  if (diff != 0)
3092  {
3093  /* There are more than one pointers that need to be updated */
3094  for (set_bits = 0, i = 0; i < diff; i++)
3095  {
3096  set_bits = 2 * set_bits + 1;
3097  }
3098  clear_bits = ~set_bits;
3099 
3100  first_ptr_offset = location & clear_bits;
3101  last_ptr_offset = location | set_bits;
3102 
3103  ehash_dir_locate (&first_page, &first_ptr_offset);
3104  ehash_dir_locate (&last_page, &last_ptr_offset);
3105  }
3106  else
3107  {
3108  /* There is only one pointer that needs to be updated */
3109  first_ptr_offset = location;
3110  ehash_dir_locate (&first_page, &first_ptr_offset);
3111  last_page = first_page;
3112  last_ptr_offset = first_ptr_offset;
3113  }
3114 
3115  /* Go over all of these pages */
3116  for (i = first_page; i <= last_page; i++)
3117  {
3118  page_p = ehash_fix_nth_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, i, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
3119  if (page_p == NULL)
3120  {
3121  return ER_FAILED;
3122  }
3123 
3124  if (i == first_page)
3125  {
3126  start_offset = first_ptr_offset;
3127  }
3128  else
3129  {
3130  start_offset = 0;
3131  }
3132 
3133  if (i == last_page)
3134  {
3135  end_offset = last_ptr_offset + sizeof (EHASH_DIR_RECORD);
3136  }
3137  else
3138  {
3139  end_offset = DB_PAGESIZE;
3140  }
3141 
3142  /* Log this page */
3143  bef_length = end_offset - start_offset;
3144  repetition.count = bef_length / sizeof (EHASH_DIR_RECORD);
3145 
3146  if (!is_temp)
3147  {
3148  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_CONNECT_BUCKET, &ehid_p->vfid, page_p, start_offset, bef_length,
3149  sizeof (EHASH_REPETITION), (char *) page_p + start_offset, &repetition);
3150  }
3151 
3152  /* Update the directory page */
3153  dir_record_p = (EHASH_DIR_RECORD *) ((char *) page_p + start_offset);
3154  for (j = 0; j < repetition.count; j++)
3155  {
3156  dir_record_p->bucket_vpid = *bucket_vpid_p;
3157  dir_record_p++;
3158  }
3159  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_p, FREE);
3160  }
3161 
3162  return NO_ERROR;
3163 }

3165 /*
3166  * ehash_find_depth () - Find depth
3167  * return: char (will return 0 in case of error)
3168  * ehid(in): identifier for the extendible hashing structure
3169  * location(in): directory entry whose neighbooring area should be checked
3170  * bucket_vpid(in): vpid of the bucket pointed by the specified directory entry
3171  * sib_vpid(in): vpid of the sibling bucket
3172  *
3173  */
3174 static char
3175 ehash_find_depth (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p, int location, VPID * bucket_vpid_p, VPID * sibling_vpid_p)
3176 {
3177  EHASH_DIR_HEADER dir_header;
3178  EHASH_DIR_RECORD *dir_record_p;
3179  PAGE_PTR page_p;
3180  int loc;
3181  int rel_loc;
3182  int iterations;
3183  int page_no;
3184  int prev_page_no;
3185  int i;
3186  unsigned int clear;
3187  char check_depth = 2;
3188  bool is_stop = false;
3189  int check_bit;
3190 
3191  prev_page_no = 0;
3192  page_p = ehash_fix_ehid_page (thread_p, ehid_p, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
3193  if (page_p == NULL)
3194  {
3195  return 0;
3196  }
3197  memcpy (&dir_header, page_p, EHASH_DIR_HEADER_SIZE);
3198 
3199  while ((check_depth <= dir_header.depth) && !is_stop)
3200  {
3201  /*
3202  * Find the base location for this iteration. The base location differs from
3203  * the original location at the check_depth bit (it has the opposite value
3204  * for this bit position) and at the remaining least significant bit
3205  * positions (it has 0 for these bit positions).
3206  */
3207  clear = 1;
3208  for (i = 1; i < check_depth - 1; i++)
3209  {
3210  clear <<= 1;
3211  clear += 1;
3212  }
3213 
3214  clear = ~clear;
3215  loc = location & clear;
3216 
3217  check_bit = GETBIT (loc, EHASH_HASH_KEY_BITS - check_depth + 1);
3218  if (check_bit != 0)
3219  {
3220  loc = CLEARBIT (loc, EHASH_HASH_KEY_BITS - check_depth + 1);
3221  }
3222  else
3223  {
3224  loc = SETBIT (loc, EHASH_HASH_KEY_BITS - check_depth + 1);
3225  }
3226 
3227  /* "loc" is the base_location now */
3228 
3229  iterations = 1 << (check_depth - 2);
3230 
3231  for (i = 0; i < iterations; i++)
3232  {
3233  rel_loc = loc | (i << 1);
3234  ehash_dir_locate (&page_no, &rel_loc);
3235  if (page_no != prev_page_no)
3236  {
3237  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_p);
3238  page_p = ehash_fix_nth_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, page_no, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
3239  if (page_p == NULL)
3240  {
3241  return 0;
3242  }
3243  prev_page_no = page_no;
3244  }
3245  dir_record_p = (EHASH_DIR_RECORD *) ((char *) page_p + rel_loc);
3246 
3247  if (!((VPID_ISNULL (&dir_record_p->bucket_vpid)) || VPID_EQ (&dir_record_p->bucket_vpid, bucket_vpid_p)
3248  || VPID_EQ (&dir_record_p->bucket_vpid, sibling_vpid_p)))
3249  {
3250  is_stop = true;
3251  break;
3252  }
3253  }
3254 
3255  if (!is_stop)
3256  {
3257  check_depth++;
3258  }
3259  }
3260 
3261  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_p);
3262  return (check_depth - 1);
3263 }

3393 /*
3394  * ehash_delete () - Delete key from ext. hashing
3395  * return: void * (NULL is returned in case of error)
3396  * ehid(in): identifier for the extendible hashing structure
3397  * key(in): Key value to remove
3398  *
3399  * Note: Deletes the given key value (together with its assoc_value)
3400  * from the specified extendible hashing structure. If the key
3401  * does not exist then it returns an error code.
3402  * After it removes the entry from the bucket page, it produces
3403  * an operational log for this deletion operation. Then, it
3404  * checks the condition of the bucket. If the bucket is empty

3406  * hashing structure and calls another function to merge the

3514  /* First insert the key type */
3515  *(short *) log_redo_record_p = bucket_recdes.type;
3516  log_redo_record_p += sizeof (short);
3517 
3518  /* Copy (the assoc-value, key) pair from the bucket record */
3519  memcpy (log_redo_record_p, bucket_recdes.data, bucket_recdes.length);
3520 
3521 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
3522  /* Check if the record contains a long string */
3523  if (bucket_recdes.type == REC_BIGONE)
3524  {
3525  ovf_vpid = *(VPID *) (bucket_recdes.data + sizeof (OID));
3526  is_long_str = true;
3527  /* Overflow pages needs to be removed, too. But, that shoud be done after the bucket record deletion has
3528  * been logged. This way, we will have the overflow pages available when logical undo-delete recovery
3529  * operation is called. Here just save the overflow page(s) id. */
3530  }
3531 #endif
3532 
3533  /* Delete the bucket record from the bucket */
3534  (void) spage_delete (thread_p, bucket_page_p, slot_no);
3535  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, bucket_page_p, DONT_FREE);
3536 
3537  /* Check the condition of bucket after the deletion */
3538  if (spage_number_of_records (bucket_page_p) <= 1)
3539  {
3540  /* Bucket became empty after this deletion */
3541  result = EHASH_BUCKET_EMPTY;
3542  }
3543  else
3544  {
3545  max_free = spage_max_space_for_new_record (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3546 
3547  /* Check if deletion had caused the Bucket to underflow, or not */
3548  if ((DB_PAGESIZE - max_free) < EHASH_UNDERFLOW_THRESHOLD)
3549  {
3550  /* Yes bucket has underflown */
3551  result = EHASH_BUCKET_UNDERFLOW;
3552  }
3553  else
3554  {
3555  /* Bucket is just fine */
3556  result = EHASH_SUCCESSFUL_COMPLETION;
3557  }
3558  }
3559 
3560  /* Log this deletion operation */
3561 
3562  if (!is_temp)
3563  {
3564  log_append_undo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_DELETE, &ehid_p->vfid, NULL, bucket_recdes.type,
3565  log_recdes_undo.length, log_recdes_undo.data);
3566 
3567  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_DELETE, &ehid_p->vfid, bucket_page_p, slot_no,
3568  log_recdes_redo.length, log_recdes_redo.data);
3569  }
3570  ehash_free_recdes (&log_recdes_undo);
3571  ehash_free_recdes (&log_recdes_redo);
3572 
3573  /* Remove the overflow pages, if any. */
3574  if (is_long_str)
3575  {
3576  (void) overflow_delete (thread_p, &dir_header_p->overflow_file, &ovf_vpid);
3577  }
3578 
3579  /* Check for the merge condition */
3580  do_merge = false; /* init */
3581  if (result == EHASH_BUCKET_EMPTY || result == EHASH_BUCKET_UNDERFLOW)
3582  {
3583  if (ehash_check_merge_possible
3584  (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_header_p, &bucket_vpid, bucket_page_p, location, S_LOCK, &old_local_depth,
3585  &sibling_vpid, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) == EHASH_SUCCESSFUL_COMPLETION)
3586  {
3587  do_merge = true;
3588  }
3589  }
3590 
3591  /* Release directory and bucket and return */
3592  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3593  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3594 
3595  /* do merge routine */
3596  if (do_merge)
3597  {
3598  ehash_merge (thread_p, ehid_p, key_p, is_temp);
3599  }
3600 
3601  return (key_p);
3602  }
3603  }
3604 }

3606 static void
3607 ehash_shrink_directory_if_need (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p, EHASH_DIR_HEADER * dir_header_p, bool is_temp)

3610

3615  i--;
3616  }

3619  {

3641  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_INC_COUNTER, &ehid_p->vfid, dir_root_page_p, offset, sizeof (int),

3646 static int
3647 ehash_merge_permanent (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p, PAGE_PTR dir_root_page_p,
3648  EHASH_DIR_HEADER * dir_header_p, PAGE_PTR bucket_page_p, PAGE_PTR sibling_page_p,
3649  VPID * bucket_vpid_p, VPID * sibling_vpid_p, int num_records, int location,
3650  PGSLOTID first_slot_id, int *out_new_local_depth_p, bool is_temp)
3651 {
3652  PGSLOTID slot_id;
3653  RECDES recdes;
3654  char *bucket_record_p;
3655  PGSLOTID new_slot_id;
3656  bool is_record_exist;
3657  int success;
3658  EHASH_BUCKET_HEADER sibling_bucket_header;
3659  char found_depth;
3660 
3661  if (!is_temp)
3662  {
3663  log_append_undo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_REPLACE, &ehid_p->vfid, sibling_page_p, 0, DB_PAGESIZE, sibling_page_p);
3664  }
3665 
3666  /* Move records of original page into the sibling bucket */
3667  for (slot_id = 1; slot_id < num_records; slot_id++)
3668  {
3669  spage_get_record (thread_p, bucket_page_p, slot_id, &recdes, PEEK);
3670  bucket_record_p = (char *) recdes.data;
3671  bucket_record_p += sizeof (OID);
3672 
3673 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
3674  if (recdes.type == REC_BIGONE) /* string type */
3675  {
3676  bucket_record_p = ehash_compose_overflow (thread_p, &recdes);
3677  if (bucket_record_p == NULL)
3678  {
3679  return ER_FAILED;
3680  }
3681  }
3682 #endif
3683 
3684  is_record_exist =
3685  ehash_locate_slot (thread_p, sibling_page_p, dir_header_p->key_type, (void *) bucket_record_p, &new_slot_id);
3686  if (is_record_exist == false)
3687  {
3688  success = spage_insert_at (thread_p, sibling_page_p, new_slot_id, &recdes);
3689  if (success != SP_SUCCESS)
3690  {
3691  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
3692 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
3693  if (recdes.type == REC_BIGONE)
3694  {
3695  free_and_init (bucket_record_p);
3696  }
3697 #endif
3698  return ER_FAILED;
3699  }
3700  }
3701  else
3702  {
3703  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_EH_CORRUPTED, 0);
3704 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
3705  if (recdes.type == REC_BIGONE)
3706  {
3707  free_and_init (bucket_record_p);
3708  }
3709 #endif
3710  return ER_FAILED;
3711  }
3712 
3713 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
3714  if (recdes.type == REC_BIGONE)
3715  {
3716  free_and_init (bucket_record_p);
3717  }
3718 #endif
3719  }
3720 
3721  found_depth = ehash_find_depth (thread_p, ehid_p, location, bucket_vpid_p, sibling_vpid_p);
3722  if (found_depth == 0)
3723  {
3724  return ER_FAILED;
3725  }
3726 
3727  /* Update the sibling header */
3728  sibling_bucket_header.local_depth = dir_header_p->depth - found_depth;
3729  *out_new_local_depth_p = sibling_bucket_header.local_depth;
3730 
3731  /* Set the record descriptor to the sib_header */
3732  recdes.data = (char *) &sibling_bucket_header;
3733  recdes.area_size = sizeof (EHASH_BUCKET_HEADER);
3734  recdes.length = sizeof (EHASH_BUCKET_HEADER);
3735  (void) spage_update (thread_p, sibling_page_p, first_slot_id, &recdes);
3736 
3737  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, sibling_page_p, DONT_FREE);
3738 
3739  if (!is_temp)
3740  {
3741  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_REPLACE, &ehid_p->vfid, sibling_page_p, 0, DB_PAGESIZE, sibling_page_p);
3742  }
3743

3747 /*
3748  * ehash_merge () - If possible, merge two buckets
3749  * return:
3750  * ehid(in): identifier for the extendible hashing structure
3751  * key(in): key value that has just been removed; used to locate the bucket.
3752  * is_temp(in): true if temporary (logging is not required)
3753  *
3754  * Note: This function checks to determine if it is possible (and
3755  * desirable) to merge the bucket (that contained the given key
3756  * before the deletion) with its sibling bucket. If so, it starts
3757  * a permanent system operation and performs the merge. And then,
3758  * it checks the size of the directory. If the directory is too
3759  * big for the remaining buckets, it shrinks the directory to
3760  * a more tolerable size before concluding the system permanent operation.
3761  */
3762 static void
3763 ehash_merge (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p, void *key_p, bool is_temp)
3764 {
3765  EHASH_DIR_HEADER *dir_header_p;
3766  PAGE_PTR dir_root_page_p;
3767  VPID bucket_vpid;
3768  PAGE_PTR bucket_page_p;
3769  PAGE_PTR sibling_page_p;
3770  VPID sibling_vpid;
3771  int location;
3772  int old_local_depth, new_local_depth;
3773  EHASH_HASH_KEY hash_key;
3774  int bucket_status;
3775  EHASH_RESULT check_result;
3776  PGSLOTID max_free;
3777  VPID null_vpid = { NULL_VOLID, NULL_PAGEID };
3778  PGSLOTID first_slot_id = -1;
3779  int num_records, sibling_location;
3780 
3781  dir_root_page_p =
3782  ehash_find_bucket_vpid_with_hash (thread_p, ehid_p, key_p, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, &bucket_vpid,
3783  &hash_key, &location);
3784  if (dir_root_page_p == NULL)
3785  {
3786  return;
3787  }
3788  dir_header_p = (EHASH_DIR_HEADER *) dir_root_page_p;
3789 
3790  if (bucket_vpid.pageid != NULL_PAGEID)
3791  {
3792  bucket_page_p = ehash_fix_old_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, &bucket_vpid, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
3793  if (bucket_page_p == NULL)
3794  {
3795  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3796  return;
3797  }
3798 
3799  /* Check the status of bucket to see if merge is still needed */
3800  if (spage_number_of_records (bucket_page_p) <= 1)
3801  {
3802  bucket_status = EHASH_BUCKET_EMPTY;
3803  }
3804  else
3805  {
3806  max_free = spage_max_space_for_new_record (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3807 
3808  /* Check if the Bucket is underflown, or not */
3809  if ((DB_PAGESIZE - max_free) < EHASH_UNDERFLOW_THRESHOLD)
3810  {
3811  bucket_status = EHASH_BUCKET_UNDERFLOW;
3812  }
3813  else
3814  {
3815  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3816  bucket_status = NO_ERROR;
3817  }
3818  }
3819 
3820  if (bucket_status == EHASH_BUCKET_EMPTY || bucket_status == EHASH_BUCKET_UNDERFLOW)
3821  {
3822  check_result =
3823  ehash_check_merge_possible (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_header_p, &bucket_vpid, bucket_page_p, location, X_LOCK,
3824  &old_local_depth, &sibling_vpid, &sibling_page_p, &first_slot_id, &num_records,
3825  &sibling_location);
3826 
3827  switch (check_result)
3828  {
3829  case EHASH_NO_SIBLING_BUCKET:
3830  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3831 
3832  if ((bucket_status == EHASH_BUCKET_EMPTY) && (old_local_depth != 0))
3833  {
3834  if (!is_temp)
3835  {
3836  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
3837  }
3838 
3839  if (file_dealloc (thread_p, &dir_header_p->bucket_file, &bucket_vpid, FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH)
3840  != NO_ERROR)
3841  {
3842  assert_release (false);
3843  }
3844 
3845  /* Set all pointers to the bucket to NULL */
3846  if (ehash_connect_bucket (thread_p, ehid_p, old_local_depth, hash_key, &null_vpid, is_temp) !=
3847  NO_ERROR)
3848  {
3849  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3850  if (!is_temp)
3851  {
3852  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
3853  }
3854  return;
3855  }
3856 
3857  ehash_adjust_local_depth (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_root_page_p, dir_header_p, old_local_depth, -1,
3858  is_temp);
3859  ehash_shrink_directory_if_need (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_header_p, is_temp);
3860  if (!is_temp)
3861  {
3862  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
3863  }
3864  }
3865  break;
3866 
3867  case EHASH_FULL_SIBLING_BUCKET:
3868  /* If the sib_bucket does not have room for the remaining records of buc_page, the record has already
3869  * been deleted, so just release bucket page */
3870  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3871  break;
3872 
3873  case EHASH_SUCCESSFUL_COMPLETION:
3874  /* Perform actual merge operation */
3875  if (!is_temp)
3876  {
3877  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
3878  }
3879 
3880  if (ehash_merge_permanent (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_root_page_p, dir_header_p, bucket_page_p, sibling_page_p,
3881  &bucket_vpid, &sibling_vpid, num_records, sibling_location, first_slot_id,
3882  &new_local_depth, is_temp) != NO_ERROR)
3883  {
3884  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, sibling_page_p);
3885  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3886  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3887  if (!is_temp)
3888  {
3889  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
3890  }
3891  return;
3892  }
3893 
3894  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, sibling_page_p);
3895  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3896 
3897  if (file_dealloc (thread_p, &dir_header_p->bucket_file, &bucket_vpid, FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH) != NO_ERROR)
3898  {
3899  assert_release (false);
3900  }
3901 
3902  ehash_adjust_local_depth (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_root_page_p, dir_header_p, old_local_depth, -2, is_temp);
3903  ehash_adjust_local_depth (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_root_page_p, dir_header_p, new_local_depth, 1, is_temp);
3904  ehash_shrink_directory_if_need (thread_p, ehid_p, dir_header_p, is_temp);
3905 
3906  /* Update some directory pointers */
3907  if (ehash_connect_bucket (thread_p, ehid_p, new_local_depth, hash_key, &sibling_vpid, is_temp)
3908  != NO_ERROR)
3909  {
3910  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3911  if (!is_temp)
3912  {
3913  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
3914  }
3915  return;
3916  }
3917 
3918  if (!is_temp)
3919  {
3920  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
3921  }
3922  break;
3923 
3924  case EHASH_ERROR_OCCURRED:
3925  /* There happened an error in the merge operation; so return */
3926 
3927  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3928  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3929  return;
3930 
3931  default:
3932  /* An undefined merge result was returned; This should never happen */
3933  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_EH_CORRUPTED, 0);
3934  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
3935  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3936  return;
3937  }
3938  }
3939  }
3940 
3941  /* Release directory and return */
3942  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
3943 }

3945 /*
3946  * ehash_shrink_directory () - Shrink directory
3947  * return:
3948  * ehid(in): identifier for the extendible hashing structure to shrink
3949  * new_depth(in): requested new depth of directory
3950  * is_temp(in): true if temporary file (logging is not required)
3951  *
3952  * Note: This function shrinks the directory of specified extendible
3953  * hashing structure as many times as necessary to attain
3954  * the requested depth. During this operation, the directory is
3955  * locked with X_LOCK to prevent others from accessing wrong
3956  * information. If the original directory is large enough, some
3957  * pages are deallocated from the new directory.
3958  * The remaining portion of the directory is logged and updated
3959  * before the extra part is deallocated.
3960  */
3961 static void
3962 ehash_shrink_directory (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p, int new_depth, bool is_temp)
3963 {
3964  int old_pages;
3965  int old_ptrs;
3966  int new_pages;
3967  int new_ptrs;
3968 
3969  EHASH_DIR_HEADER *dir_header_p;
3970  int end_offset;
3971  int new_end_offset;
3972  int check_pages;
3973  int i;
3974  int times;
3975 
3976  PAGE_PTR old_dir_page_p;
3977  int old_dir_offset;
3978  int old_dir_nth_page;
3979  int prev_pg_no;
3980 
3981  PAGE_PTR new_dir_page_p;
3982  PGLENGTH new_dir_offset;
3983  int new_dir_nth_page;
3984  int ret = NO_ERROR;
3985 
3986  dir_header_p = (EHASH_DIR_HEADER *) ehash_fix_nth_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, 0, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
3987  if (dir_header_p == NULL)
3988  {
3989  return;
3990  }
3991 
3992  if (dir_header_p->depth < new_depth)
3993  {
3994 #ifdef EHASH_DEBUG
3995  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "WARNING in eh_shrink_dir:The directory has a depth of %d , shrink is cancelled ",
3996  dir_header_p->depth);
3997 #endif
3998  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, (PAGE_PTR) dir_header_p);
3999  return;
4000  }
4001 
4002  old_ptrs = 1 << dir_header_p->depth;
4003  times = 1 << (dir_header_p->depth - new_depth);
4004  ret = file_get_num_user_pages (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, &old_pages);
4005  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4006  {
4007 #ifdef EHASH_DEBUG
4008  er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "WARNING: error reading user page number from file, shrink is cancelled.\n");
4009 #endif
4010  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4011  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, (PAGE_PTR) dir_header_p);
4012  return;
4013  }
4014  old_pages -= 1; /* The first page starts with 0 */
4015 
4016  new_ptrs = old_ptrs / times; /* Calculate how many pointers will remain */
4017 
4018  end_offset = old_ptrs - 1; /* Directory first pointer has an offset of 0 */
4019  ehash_dir_locate (&check_pages, &end_offset);
4020 #ifdef EHASH_DEBUG
4021  if (check_pages != old_pages)
4022  {
4023  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_EH_ROOT_CORRUPTED, 3, ehid_p->vfid.volid, ehid_p->vfid.fileid,
4024  ehid_p->pageid);
4025  return;
4026  }
4027 #endif
4028 
4029  /* Perform shrink */
4030 
4031  prev_pg_no = 0;
4032  old_dir_page_p = ehash_fix_nth_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, prev_pg_no, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
4033  if (old_dir_page_p == NULL)
4034  {
4035  return;
4036  }
4037 
4038  new_dir_nth_page = 0;
4039  new_dir_page_p = (PAGE_PTR) dir_header_p;
4040  new_dir_offset = EHASH_DIR_HEADER_SIZE;
4041 
4042  if (!is_temp)
4043  {
4044  log_append_undo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_REPLACE, &ehid_p->vfid, new_dir_page_p, 0, DB_PAGESIZE, new_dir_page_p);
4045  }
4046 
4047  dir_header_p->depth = new_depth; /* Decrease the directory global depth */
4048 
4049  /* Copy old directory records to new (shrunk) area */
4050  for (i = 1; i < new_ptrs; i++)
4051  {
4052  /* Location 0 will not change */
4053 
4054  /* Locate the next source pointer */
4055  old_dir_offset = i * times;
4056  ehash_dir_locate (&old_dir_nth_page, &old_dir_offset);
4057 
4058  if (old_dir_nth_page != prev_pg_no)
4059  {
4060  /* We reached the end of the source page. The next bucket pointer is in the next Dir page */
4061 
4062  prev_pg_no = old_dir_nth_page;
4063  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, old_dir_page_p);
4064 
4065  /* set olddir_pgptr to the new pgptr */
4066  old_dir_page_p = ehash_fix_nth_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, old_dir_nth_page, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
4067  if (old_dir_page_p == NULL)
4068  {
4069  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, new_dir_page_p, FREE);
4070  return;
4071  }
4072  }
4073 
4074  /* Advance the destination pointer to new spot */
4075  new_dir_offset += sizeof (EHASH_DIR_RECORD);
4076 
4077  if ((DB_PAGESIZE - new_dir_offset) < SSIZEOF (EHASH_DIR_RECORD))
4078  {
4079  /* There is no more place in the directory page for new bucket pointers */
4080 
4081  if (!is_temp)
4082  {
4083  /* Log this updated directory page */
4084  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_REPLACE, &ehid_p->vfid, new_dir_page_p, 0, DB_PAGESIZE,
4085  new_dir_page_p);
4086  }
4087 
4088  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, new_dir_page_p, FREE);
4089 
4090  /* get another page */
4091  new_dir_nth_page++;
4092 
4093  /* set newdir_pgptr to the new pgptr */
4094  new_dir_page_p = ehash_fix_nth_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, new_dir_nth_page, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
4095  if (new_dir_page_p == NULL)
4096  {
4097  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, old_dir_page_p);
4098  return;
4099  }
4100  new_dir_offset = 0;
4101 
4102  if (!is_temp)
4103  {
4104  /* Log the initial content of this directory page */
4105  log_append_undo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_REPLACE, &ehid_p->vfid, new_dir_page_p, 0, DB_PAGESIZE,
4106  new_dir_page_p);
4107  }
4108  }
4109 
4110  /* Perform the copy operation */
4111  memcpy ((char *) new_dir_page_p + new_dir_offset, (char *) old_dir_page_p + old_dir_offset,
4112  sizeof (EHASH_DIR_RECORD));
4113  }
4114 
4115  if (!is_temp)
4116  {
4117  /* Log this updated directory page */
4118  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_REPLACE, &ehid_p->vfid, new_dir_page_p, 0, DB_PAGESIZE, new_dir_page_p);
4119  }
4120 
4121  /* Release the source and destination pages */
4122  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, old_dir_page_p);
4123  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, new_dir_page_p, FREE);
4124 
4125  /* remove unwanted part of directory. */
4126  new_end_offset = new_ptrs - 1;
4127  ehash_dir_locate (&new_pages, &new_end_offset);
4128  ret = file_numerable_truncate (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, new_pages + 1);
4129  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4130  {
4131  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4132  }
4133 }

4135 static EHASH_HASH_KEY
4136 ehash_hash_string_type (char *key_p, char *original_key_p)
4137 {
4138  EHASH_HASH_KEY hash_key = 0;
4139  char copy_psekey[12];
4140  int i;
4141  int length;
4142  int times;
4143  int remaining;
4144  int Int;
4145  char Char;
4146  int byte;
4147  char *p = NULL;
4148  char *new_key_p = NULL;
4149 
4150  length = (int) strlen (key_p);
4151 
4152  if (length > 0)
4153  {
4154  /* Eliminate any trailing space characters */
4155  if (char_isspace (*(char *) (key_p + length - 1)))
4156  {
4157  for (p = key_p + length - 1; char_isspace (*p) && (p > key_p); p--)
4158  {
4159  ;
4160  }
4161  length = (int) (p - key_p + 1);
4162  key_p = new_key_p = (char *) malloc (length + 1); /* + 1 is for \0 */
4163  if (key_p == NULL)
4164  {
4165  return 0;
4166  }
4167  memcpy (key_p, original_key_p, length);
4168  *(char *) (key_p + length) = '\0';
4169  }
4170 
4171  /* Takes the floor of division */
4172  times = length / sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY);
4173 
4174  /* Apply Folding method */
4175  for (i = 1; i <= times; i++)
4176  {
4177  memcpy (&Int, key_p, sizeof (int));
4178  hash_key += Int; /* Add next word of original key */
4179 
4180  key_p += sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY);
4181  }
4182 
4183  remaining = length - times * sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY);
4184 
4185  /* Go over the remaining chars of key */
4186  for (i = 1; i <= remaining; i++)
4187  {
4188  /* shift left to align with previous content */
4189  Int = (int) *key_p++ << i;
4190  hash_key += Int;
4191  }
4192 
4193  if (new_key_p)
4194  {
4195  free_and_init (new_key_p);
4196  }
4197  }
4198 
4199  /* Copy the hash_key to an aux. area, to be further hashed into individual bytes */
4200  memcpy (&copy_psekey, &hash_key, sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY));
4201  copy_psekey[sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY)] = '\0';
4202 
4203  hash_key = 0;
4204  byte = mht_1strhash (copy_psekey, 509);
4205  hash_key = hash_key + (byte << (8 * (sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY) - 1)));
4206  byte = mht_2strhash (copy_psekey, 509);
4207  hash_key = hash_key + (byte << (8 * (sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY) - 2)));
4208  byte = mht_3strhash (copy_psekey, 509);
4209  hash_key = hash_key + (byte << (8 * (sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY) - 3)));
4210 
4211  /* Go over the chars of the given pseudo key */
4212  Char = '\0';
4213  key_p = (char *) &copy_psekey;
4214  for (i = 0; (unsigned int) i < sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY); i++)
4215  {
4216  Char += (char) *key_p++;
4217  }
4218 
4219  /* Change the first byte of the pseudo key to the SUM of all of them */
4220  return hash_key + Char;
4221 }

4223 static EHASH_HASH_KEY
4224 ehash_hash_eight_bytes_type (char *key_p)
4225 {
4226  EHASH_HASH_KEY hash_key = 0;
4227  unsigned int i;
4228  int Int;
4229  char Char;
4230 
4231  for (i = 0; i < sizeof (double) / sizeof (int); i++)
4232  {
4233  memcpy (&Int, key_p, sizeof (int));
4234  hash_key += htonl (Int); /* Add next word of original key */
4235  key_p += sizeof (int);
4236  }
4237 
4238  /* Go over the chars of the given pseudo key */
4239  Char = '\0';
4240  key_p = (char *) &hash_key;
4241  for (i = 0; i < sizeof (EHASH_HASH_KEY); i++)
4242  {
4243  Char ^= (char) *key_p++;
4244  }
4245 
4246  /* Change the first byte of the pseudo key to the summation of all of them */
4247  memcpy (&hash_key, &Char, sizeof (char));
4248 
4249  return hash_key;
4250 }

4310 /*
4311  * ehash_hash () - Hash function
4312  * return: EHASH_HASH_KEY
4313  * orig_key(in): original key to encode into a pseudo key
4314  * key_type(in): type of the key
4315  *
4316  * Note: This function converts the given original key into a pseudo
4317  * key. Since the original key is presented as a character
4318  * string, its conversion into a int-compatible type is essential
4319  * prior to performing any operation on it.
4320  * Depending on the "key_type", the original key might be
4321  * folded (for DB_TYPE_STRING, DB_TYPE_OBJECT and DB_TYPE_DOUBLE) or duplicated
4322  * (for DB_TYPE_SHORT) into a computer word.
4323  * This function does not change the value of parameter
4324  * orig_key, as it might be on a bucket.
4325  */
4326 static EHASH_HASH_KEY
4327 ehash_hash (void *original_key_p, DB_TYPE key_type)
4328 {
4329  char *key = (char *) original_key_p;
4330  EHASH_HASH_KEY hash_key = 0;
4331 
4332  switch (key_type)
4333  {
4334  case DB_TYPE_STRING:
4335  hash_key = ehash_hash_string_type (key, (char *) original_key_p);
4336  break;
4337 
4338  case DB_TYPE_OBJECT:
4339  hash_key = ehash_hash_eight_bytes_type (key);
4340  break;
4341 
4342 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
4343  case DB_TYPE_BIGINT:
4344  case DB_TYPE_DOUBLE:
4345  case DB_TYPE_MONETARY:
4346  if (key_type == DB_TYPE_MONETARY)
4347  {
4348  key = (char *) &(((DB_MONETARY *) original_key_p)->amount);
4349  }
4350 
4351  hash_key = ehash_hash_eight_bytes_type (key);
4352  break;
4353 
4354  case DB_TYPE_FLOAT:
4355  case DB_TYPE_DATE:
4356  case DB_TYPE_TIME:
4357  case DB_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
4358  case DB_TYPE_DATETIME:
4359  case DB_TYPE_INTEGER:
4360  hash_key = ehash_hash_four_bytes_type (key);
4361  break;
4362 
4363  case DB_TYPE_SHORT:
4364  hash_key = ehash_hash_two_bytes_type (key);
4365  break;
4366 #endif
4367  default:
4368  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_EH_CORRUPTED, 0);
4369  }
4370 
4371  return hash_key;
4372 }

4426 /*
4427  * eh_count () - Find how many entries are kept in the ext. hashing structure
4428  * return: int
4429  * ehid(in): identifier of the extendible hashing structure
4430  *
4431  * Note: Find outs and returns the total number of entries (i.e., the
4432  * key and assoc_value pairs) stored in the specified extendible
4433  * hashing structure. If an error occurs in finding this
4434  * information, -1 is returned.
4435  *
4436  * Note that the total number of entries of an extendible hashing
4437  * structure is not a stored piece of information. (Keeping a
4438  * counter for this purpose would put an extra overhead to
4439  * insertion and deletion operations). Instead, it is calculated
4440  * by this function whenever it is desired. It is calculated by
4441  * fetching all of the bucket pages of the extendible hashing
4442  * structure and adding up the number of entries existing in each
4443  * bucket. Consequently, this function is quite expensive, and it
4444  * should not be called very often.
4445  */
4446 int
4447 eh_count (EHID * ehid)
4448 {
4449  int num_entries; /* Total number of entries contained in the extendible hashing structure; will be the
4450  * return value */
4451  int numpages; /* Number of bucket pages */
4452 
4453  /* Local variables for the directory */
4454  EHASH_DIR_HEADER *dir_header;
4455  PAGE_PTR dir_pgptr;
4456 
4457  /* Local variables for the buckets */
4458  PAGE_PTR buc_pgptr;
4459  int buc_pg_no;
4460 
4461  if (ehid == NULL)
4462  {
4463  return 0;
4464  }
4465 
4466  /* Access root page of the directory */
4467  dir_pgptr = ehash_fix_ehid_page (ehid, PGBUF_LATCH_READ);
4468  if (dir_pgptr == NULL)
4469  {
4470  return -1;
4471  }
4472  dir_header = (EHASH_DIR_HEADER *) dir_pgptr;
4473 
4474  numpages = file_get_numpages (&dir_header->bucket_file);
4475  num_entries = 0;
4476 
4477  for (buc_pg_no = 0; buc_pg_no < numpages; buc_pg_no++)
4478  {
4479  /* set buc_pgptr to the next bucket page */
4480 
4481  buc_pgptr = ehhash_fix_nth_page (&dir_header->bucket_file, buc_pg_no, PGBUF_LATCH_READ);
4482  if (buc_pgptr == NULL)
4483  {
4484  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_pgptr);
4485  return -1;
4486  }
4487 
4488  /* Add the number of entries kept in this bucket page to the global sum */
4489 
4490  num_entries += spage_number_of_records (buc_pgptr) - 1; /* Minus 1 is for the first record (page header) */
4491  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, buc_pgptr);
4492  }
4493 
4494  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_pgptr);
4495 
4496  return num_entries;
4497 }

4684  *temp_p++ = *bucket_record_p++;

4744  *out_apply_error = (*apply_function) (thread_p, key_p, assoc_value_p, args);

4754 /*
4755  * ehash_map () - Apply function to all entries
4756  * return: int NO_ERROR, or ER_FAILED
4757  * ehid(in): identifier of the extendible hashing structure
4758  * fun(in): function to call on key, data, and arguments
4759  * args(in):
4760  *
4761  */
4762 int
4763 ehash_map (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p,
4764  int (*apply_function) (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, void *key, void *data, void *args), void *args)
4765 {
4766  EHASH_DIR_HEADER *dir_header_p;
4767  int num_pages, bucket_page_no, num_records;
4768  PAGE_PTR dir_page_p, bucket_page_p = NULL;
4769  char *bucket_record_p;
4770  RECDES recdes;
4771  PGSLOTID slot_id, first_slot_id = NULL_SLOTID;
4772  OID assoc_value;
4773  int apply_error_code = NO_ERROR;
4774 
4775  if (ehid_p == NULL)
4776  {
4777  return ER_FAILED;
4778  }
4779 
4780  dir_page_p = ehash_fix_ehid_page (thread_p, ehid_p, PGBUF_LATCH_READ);
4781  if (dir_page_p == NULL)
4782  {
4783  return ER_FAILED;
4784  }
4785 
4786  dir_header_p = (EHASH_DIR_HEADER *) dir_page_p;
4787  if (file_get_num_user_pages (thread_p, &dir_header_p->bucket_file, &num_pages) != NO_ERROR)
4788  {
4789  return ER_FAILED;
4790  }
4791 
4792  /* Retrieve each bucket page and apply the given function to its entries */
4793  for (bucket_page_no = 0; apply_error_code == NO_ERROR && bucket_page_no < num_pages; bucket_page_no++)
4794  {
4795  first_slot_id = NULL_SLOTID;
4796  bucket_page_p = ehash_fix_nth_page (thread_p, &dir_header_p->bucket_file, bucket_page_no, PGBUF_LATCH_READ);
4797  if (bucket_page_p == NULL)
4798  {
4799  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_page_p);
4800  return ER_FAILED;
4801  }
4802 
4803  num_records = spage_number_of_records (bucket_page_p);
4804 
4805  (void) spage_next_record (bucket_page_p, &first_slot_id, &recdes, PEEK);
4806 
4807  /* Skip the first slot since it contains the bucket header */
4808  for (slot_id = first_slot_id + 1; apply_error_code == NO_ERROR && slot_id < num_records; slot_id++)
4809  {
4810  (void) spage_get_record (thread_p, bucket_page_p, slot_id, &recdes, PEEK);
4811  bucket_record_p = (char *) recdes.data;
4812  bucket_record_p = ehash_read_oid_from_record (bucket_record_p, &assoc_value);
4813 
4814  if (ehash_apply_each (thread_p, ehid_p, &recdes, dir_header_p->key_type, bucket_record_p, &assoc_value,
4815  &apply_error_code, apply_function, args) != NO_ERROR)
4816  {
4817  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
4818  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_page_p);
4819  return ER_FAILED;
4820  }
4821  }
4822  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
4823  }
4824 
4825  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_page_p);
4826 
4827  return apply_error_code;
4828 }

5260 /*
5261  * xeh_find () -
5262  * return: error code
5263  * ehid(in): hash table identifier
5264  * value(in): : key value
5265  * oid(in): oid registered under key value if any (returned)
5266  *
5267  * Note: This was designed for the maintenance of the UNIQUE integrity
5268  * constraint. The only difference between this and ehash_search is that
5269  * the DB_TYPE is supplied as a parameter.
5270  * This is necessary so that the network interface can determine how
5271  * long the key value is and pack it appropriately into the transfer buffer.
5272  */
5273 EH_SEARCH
5274 xeh_find (EHID * ehid, void *value, OID * oid)
5275 {

5277  OID current;
5278 
5279  status = ehash_search (ehid, value, &current);
5280 
5281  if (status == EH_KEY_FOUND)

5556 /*
5557  * ehash_rv_delete () - Recovery delete function
5558  * return: int
5559  * ehid(in): identifier for the extendible hashing structure
5560  * key(in): Key value to remove
5561  *
5562  * Note: This is the recovery version of the "ehash_delete" function. Just
5563  * like the original function, this one also deletes the given
5564  * key value (together with its assoc_value) from the specified
5565  * extendible hashing structure, and returns an error code if the
5566  * key does not exist. However, unlike "ehash_delete", it does not
5567  * check the condition of bucket and invoke "eh_try_to_merge"
5568  * when possible. Nor does it produce undo log information. (It
5569  * merely produces redo log to produce the compansating log
5570  * record for this operation. This is to minimize the recovery
5571  * and transaction abort activities.)
5572  */
5573 static int
5574 ehash_rv_delete (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, EHID * ehid_p, void *key_p)
5575 {
5576  EHASH_DIR_HEADER *dir_header_p;
5577  PAGE_PTR dir_root_page_p;
5578  VPID bucket_vpid;
5579  PAGE_PTR bucket_page_p;
5580  PGSLOTID slot_no;
5581 
5582  RECDES bucket_recdes;
5583  RECDES log_recdes_redo;
5584  char *log_redo_record_p;
5585  int error = NO_ERROR;
5586 
5587  dir_root_page_p =
5588  ehash_find_bucket_vpid_with_hash (thread_p, ehid_p, key_p, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, &bucket_vpid, NULL,
5589  NULL);
5590  if (dir_root_page_p == NULL)
5591  {
5592  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5593  return er_errid ();
5594  }
5595  dir_header_p = (EHASH_DIR_HEADER *) dir_root_page_p;
5596 
5597  if (bucket_vpid.pageid == NULL_PAGEID)
5598  {
5599  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
5600  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_EH_UNKNOWN_KEY, 0);
5601  return ER_EH_UNKNOWN_KEY;
5602  }
5603  else
5604  {
5605  bucket_page_p = ehash_fix_old_page (thread_p, &ehid_p->vfid, &bucket_vpid, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
5606  if (bucket_page_p == NULL)
5607  {
5608  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
5609 
5610  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
5611  return er_errid ();
5612  }
5613 
5614  /* Try to delete key from buc_page */
5615 
5616  /* Check if deletion possible, or not */
5617  if (ehash_locate_slot (thread_p, bucket_page_p, dir_header_p->key_type, key_p, &slot_no) == false)
5618  {
5619  /* Key does not exist, so return errorcode */
5620  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
5621  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
5622  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_EH_UNKNOWN_KEY, 0);
5623  return ER_EH_UNKNOWN_KEY;
5624  }
5625  else
5626  {
5627  /* Key exists in the bucket */
5628 
5629  /* Put the redo (compansating) log record */
5630  (void) spage_get_record (thread_p, bucket_page_p, slot_no, &bucket_recdes, PEEK);
5631 
5632  /* Prepare the redo log record */
5633  if (ehash_allocate_recdes (&log_recdes_redo, bucket_recdes.length + sizeof (short), REC_HOME) == NULL)
5634  {
5635  /*
5636  * Will not be able to log a compensating log record... continue
5637  * anyhow...without the log...since we are doing recovery anyhow
5638  */
5639  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
5640  }
5641  else
5642  {
5643  log_redo_record_p = log_recdes_redo.data;
5644 
5645  /* First insert the key type */
5646  *(short *) log_redo_record_p = bucket_recdes.type;
5647  log_redo_record_p += sizeof (short);
5648 
5649  /* Copy (the assoc-value, key) pair from the bucket record */
5650  memcpy (log_redo_record_p, bucket_recdes.data, bucket_recdes.length);
5651 
5652  /* why is redo logged inside an undo? */
5653  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVEH_DELETE, &ehid_p->vfid, bucket_page_p, slot_no,
5654  log_recdes_redo.length, log_recdes_redo.data);
5655 
5656  ehash_free_recdes (&log_recdes_redo);
5657  }
5658 
5659  /* Delete the bucket record from the bucket; */
5660  (void) spage_delete (thread_p, bucket_page_p, slot_no);
5661  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, bucket_page_p, DONT_FREE);
5662 
5663  /* Do not remove the overflow pages here */
5664  /* Since they will be removed by their own undo functions */
5665  }
5666  }
5667 
5668  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, bucket_page_p);
5669  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, dir_root_page_p);
5670 
5671  return error;
5672 }
